article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 54, Stephen F. Austin 49
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Isaiah Allen hit the go-ahead 3-pointer with 33 seconds left, and Texas-San Antonio snapped a seven-game losing streak by beating Stephen F. Austin 54-49 Saturday. Allen finished with 13 points and Kurt Attaway hit two free throws with 13 seconds left to seal the win for the Roadrunners (7-22, 3-13 Southland Conference). Keith Hardaway scored 10 points for Stephen F. Austin (15-13, 8-8), but his 3-point attempt that would have tied the game missed with 16 seconds left. Earlier, Hardaway hit a 3-pointer that tied the game at 49 with 1:16 remaining. Melvin Smith scored 14 points for UTSA. Stephen F. Austin led 46-39 with 4:29 left before Texas-San Antonio rallied by scoring the next 10 points.
